commit.message: Updated the README.md file for Ubuntu packages
Updated the README.md file for Ubuntu packages

Fixed an issue, where the data in the liststore
became out of sync with the data on the filesystem,
causing duplicate todos to be created when
modifying them

Made the selection a tiny bit safer,
on the off chance they click, but somehow find a pixel not
in the tree.

Also removed a debugging line.

bug: In 1.8.x, clicking on a todo on the datebook, took one to the todo screen, and selected the todo you clicked on.  While this
was taking one to the todo screen, it was not selecting the todo you clicked on.
This change fixes that.

The issue was selection function was being invoked after the call to the button release event, causing the glob_find_id to end up getting reset to 0.

This change gets rid of the selection function, and relies on the button press event.

bug: In 1.8.x, clicking on the 'checkbox' image would save the change.
In 2.0.x, the checkbox would get 'clicked', but not persisted.
So if you left the view, or changed category, the checkbox would reset
to the previous value (checked or unchecked).
This persists the checkbox change to the pc, which survives the refreshes, and restores the behavior in 1.8.
Made suggested changes to default css file.
Bump version to 2.0.1

commit.message:
added check for NULL on field2
before blindly calling strcmp.
It probably won't ever be NULL,
but just in case.

modified loading preferences to load new theme
if old theme existed.  This should make the upgrade
a bit easier for those using one of the themes other
than default.  To account for the theme filename change,
attempted to 'rename' the theme if it was using
one of the default rc files bundled with jpilot
to the css equivalent.
set gtk_cell_renderer_set_fixed_size to 18 height

set default css to be the default.
This should at least set the css file,
and when you open the preferences menu for theme,
it should be selected instead of not being set.
